{These are the most typical sacrifices in Andersson's games. Playing for a win
when material down creates a certain feel of magic. In Andersson-Larsen
White's compensation (actually more than that, we should call it advantage)
consisted of his mobile and massive center. In Kharlov-Andersson Black's main
trumps were his perfect stability and the coordination between the rook,
bishop and the passed pawn.}  *

