{[#]White has an extra pawn (a strong defended passed pawn actually) and the
bishops' pair. Which is the best way of neutralizing Black's light initiative?
} 35. Be5 $1 {This is the strongest move, preventing the blocking ...Nd6.} (35.
Kg2 $6 {This maintains only part of the advantage as Black can force the
transposition to an ending with opposite-colored bishops.} Nh4+ 36. Kf2 Nf3 {
[%cal Gf3d2] Threatening ...Nd2.} 37. Kxf3 Rxf1+ 38. Ke3 Bg4 39. Rg2 h5 $14) (
35. Kf2 $6 {This move, played in the game, allows Black to equalize. See the
next test.}) 35... Bd7 36. Kf2 $16 *

