{[#]Black has an equalizing forced variation at his disposal.} 35... Nd6 $1 {
The perfect blockade, as the knight also attacks c4.} 36. Kg2 (36. Rc2 Bf5 {
and the rook cannot leave the second rank due to ...Rd2+.}) 36... Bh3+ $1 {
The bishops' exchange makes the weakness on c4 chronical.} (36... Nxc4 $2 37.
Rf2+ $1 {followed by Bxc4.}) 37. Kxh3 Rxf1 38. bxc5 bxc5 39. Kg2 Rf5 $1 {
The simplest. The rook retreats along the f-file in order to be ready for ...
Rf4 on the next move.} (39... Rf4 $2 40. Be5) (39... Rb1 $6 {This should also
lead to a draw, but in a rook ending with a pawn down.} 40. Rc2 Nxc4 41. Bc1
Nb6 42. Rxc5 Nxd5 43. Rxd5 Rxc1 44. Rd7+ Ke6 45. Rxa7 Rc3 $11) 40. Rc2 Rf4 $1 (
40... Kg6 $6 41. Bc1 Rf6 42. Be3 Ne4 43. Rb2 $14 {Sokolov,V-Andersson,U Wijk
aan Zee 1970 (0-1, 56)}) 41. Be5 Rxc4 42. Rf2+ Ke7 43. Rf6 Rg4+ 44. Kf3 Rg6 $11
*

