{[#]Black's strong knight ensures him an obvious advantage but he has to deal
with the positional threat f4-f5. Your move.} 25... Rd4 $1 {Centralizing the
rook and attacking c4.} (25... Rd2 $6 26. f5 Bc8 27. Rb1 $132) 26. Rd1 (26. f5
$2 Bxc4) 26... Bg4+ $1 {From a practical point of view the most simple
decision. Black forces an ending where his knight is stronger than the bishop.}
(26... Bh3 $1 {was also strong. After 27.Rh1, you are invited to find the win
in the next test.}) 27. Nxg4 hxg4+ 28. Kxg4 Rxc4 (28... Rxd1 $6 29. Bxd1 Nxe4
30. Bc2 (30. Ba4 c5 31. fxe5 Ke6 32. Kf4 $11) 30... Nd2 31. Ba4 (31. f5 gxf5+
32. Kxf5 Nxc4 33. Ba4 $132) 31... c5 (31... e4 $1 $19) 32. f5 Nxc4 33. fxg6
fxg6 34. Kf3 Nxa3 35. Ke4 c4 {0-1 Solmundarson,M-Andersson,U Reykjavik 1972})
29. Bb1 a4 $17 *

