{[#]The structure is symmetrical, the material equal and both players seem to
have normal coordination. And still, White wins by force!} 40. Ne5 $1 {As
strange as this may seem, White wins a piece by force. Black is in some sort
of Zugzwang.} Nd8 (40... Bd6 41. Rxf7#) (40... Rc1 41. Rc7 {and Black does not
have ...Nb4 or ...Nxd4 anymore.}) 41. Rd7 Rb2 (41... Ra2 {allows} 42. f4 {
followed by g4-g5+ or fxg5+ soon, in both cases winning the bishop.}) 42. Ba5
$1 (42. f4 $6 Rb7 $1) 42... Nb7 43. Bc7 {Black remains paralyzed.} Rb1+ 44. Kg2
Rb2 (44... Rb3 45. f4 $18) 45. Nd3 $1 {1-0 Andersson,U-Williams,A Skopje 1972}
Rb3 46. Be5+ Kg6 47. Rxe7 Rxd3 48. Rxb7 $18 *

