{[#]Due to his better structure and piece activity Black has a clear advantage.
However, White defends all the important squares along the c-file so an
immediate intrusion is not possible. How to make progress?} 31... Rc8 $1 {
A typical Ulf rook retreat, aiming to take the backward pawn on b3 under
observation.} 32. Bd2 Rb8 33. Nc1 Nb4 34. Bxb4 (34. Ra3 Bb2 {wins material.})
34... Rxb4 35. Rf2 {Black's progress is obvious, but he can increase his
pressure even more.} Be7 $1 {Another retreat, aiming to increase the pressure
on f4.} 36. Rf3 Bd6 37. Ne2 Re4 38. Rd3 Bc5 39. Rc3 Bf2 40. Rc2 Kg7 41. Ng1
Rxf4 42. Nf3 Bg3 43. Kg1 Re4 44. Kf1 Re3 45. Rb2 e5 46. Rb1 e4 {0-1 Vogt,
L-Andersson, U Cienfuegos 1975} *

