{[#]Why was Black's last move a mistake?} 30. Ra1 $1 {White starts the fight
against Black's slightly contorted pieces.} Nb4 31. Bxb4 (31. Nxb4 {should
also win, even though the process would be more laborious:} axb4 32. Kc2 bxa3
33. Kxb3 axb2 34. Kxb2 e5 {The only chance.} 35. Kc3 Ke4 36. Kd2 exd4 37. exd4
Bxd4 38. Ra4 $1 {This pin will prove lethal as Black needs to weaken his
kingside in order to avoid an immediate loss.} g4 (38... Ke5 39. f4+ gxf4 40.
gxf4+ Ke4 41. Ke2 h4 42. h3 f6 43. Rb4 $18 {and Black loses the bishop due to
Zugzwang soon.}) 39. Ke2 Ke5 40. f4+ gxf3+ 41. Kxf3 $18 {Black's pawns'
weakness is decisive despite the almost equal material.}) 31... axb4 32. Rb1 {
Threatening Na1.} Ke4 33. Ne1 $1 {Parrying ...Rd3 and threatening Kc2.} (33.
Na1 $2 Rd3+ 34. Ke2 g4 $1 $11) 33... Bxd4 {Desperation.} 34. exd4 Kxd4 35. Kc2
Kc4 36. Ra1 d4 37. Ra7 d3+ {, and Black resigned without waiting for his
opponent's answer, 1-0 Andersson,U (2565)-Jovicic,M (2200) Belgrad 1977 After}
38. Nxd3 Rxd3 39. Rc7+ Kd4 40. Rd7+ {wins the rook.} *

