{[#]White to move and draw.} 54. Kh6 $1 {This is the correct move, creating
counterplay just in time.} (54. axb4 $2 {This natural move is the decisive
mistake, as Black's candidate to promotion will be on the fourth rank already,
while there was no progress for White on the last move.} cxb4 55. Kh6 a3 56. e7
(56. bxa3 bxa3 57. e7 {does not change anything.} Kxe7 58. Kg7 a2 59. f6+ Ke6
60. f7 a1=Q+) 56... Kxe7 57. Kg7 axb2 58. f6+ Kd7 59. f7 b1=Q 60. f8=Q Qg1+ {
0-1 Quinteros, M (2505)-Andersson, U (2610) Mar del Plata 1981. Black will
force the queen exchange soon:} 61. Kh6 (61. Kh7 Qh2+ 62. Kg8 Qg3+ 63. Kh7 Qh4+
64. Kg8 Qd8) 61... Qe3+ 62. Kg6 (62. Kg7 Qe7+) 62... Qe8+) 54... c4 55. e7 Kxe7
56. Kg7 c3 57. f6+ Kd7 58. bxc3 bxa3 59. f7 a2 60. f8=Q $11 *

