{[#]Both sides have two connected passed pawns, but White's are more advanced.
Black has only one saving move.} 55... Kb8 $3 {The only move which allows
Black to answer either pawn's advance properly and reach the critical mutual
Zugzwang position with White to move!} (55... Kd6 $2 56. b6 (56. a6 {also wins.
} Kc7 57. a7 Kb7 58. b6 Ka8 59. Kc4 Kb7 60. Kxc5 d3 61. Kd6 d2 62. a8=Q+ Kxa8
63. Kc7) 56... Kd7 (56... Kc6 57. Kc4 {transposes above.}) 57. a6 Kc6 58. a7
Kb7 59. Kc4 Ka8 60. Kxc5 Kb7 61. Kd6 d3 62. a8=Q+ Kxa8 63. Kc7 d2 64. b7+ {
1-0 Andersson, U-Green, E Stockholm 1969}) (55... Kb7 $2 56. b6 Kc6 57. Kc4 {
reaches the mutual Zugzwang position with Black to move.} h6 58. h3 Kb7 59. Kb5
d3 60. a6+ Kb8 (60... Ka8 61. Kc6 d2 62. b7+ Ka7 63. Kc7) 61. Kc6 d2 62. a7+
Ka8 63. b7+ Kxa7 64. Kc7 d1=Q 65. b8=Q+ Ka6 66. Qb6#) 56. Kc4 (56. b6 Kb7 {
transposes}) (56. a6 Ka7 57. Kc4 Kb6 $11) 56... Kb7 57. b6 Kc6 $11 {In the
game this position could have arisen with Black to move.} *

