{[#]Can Black still fight for an advantage?} 44... f4+ $1 {The best practical
chance. Black clears the f5-square for the second pawn in order to get a
reserve tempo and prevents Ke3-f4.} (44... Kd5 $6 {leads to a simple draw.} 45.
Kf4 Kc4 46. Kxf5 Kc3 47. g4 hxg4 48. hxg4 Kb2 49. Kxf6 Kxa2 50. g5 $11) (44...
b5 $6 {already allows} 45. f4+ {when Black has committed his second b-pawn too
soon with respect to similar lines from the previous test.} Kd5 46. Kd3 Kc5 47.
Kc2 Kc4 (47... Kd4 48. Kb3 $11) 48. Kb2 Kd3 49. Kb3 Ke3 50. Kxb4 h4 51. gxh4
Kxf4 52. Kxb5 Kg3 53. h5 f4 $11) 45. gxf4+ Kd5 46. Kd3 f5 47. h4 Kc5 {In the
next test you will have to find the best move for White.} *

